Experiment 1.1 contains dupliacate (Leetcode 217)
Aim: 
Given an integer array nums, return true if any value appears at least twice in the array, and return false if every element is distinct.

Algorithm:
1. Start.
2. Take the input array num.
3. Sort the array in ascending order.
4. Traverse the sorted array from the second element (i = 1) to the last element.
5. Compare the current element num[i] with the previous element num[i - 1].
6. If both elements are equal, return true because a duplicate is found.
7. If the loop completes without finding any duplicate, return false.
8. End

Code:
class Solution {
public:
    bool containsDuplicate(vector<int>& num) {
        sort(num.begin(), num.end());
        for(int i=1;i<num.size();i++){
            if(num[i]==num[i-1]){
                return true;
            }
        }
        return false;
    }
};

Experiment 1.2 Contains Dupllicate 2 (Leetcode 219)
Aim:
Given an integer array nums and an integer k, return true if there are two distinct indices i and j in the array such that nums[i] == nums[j] and abs(i - j) <= k.

Algorithm:
1. Start.
2. Create an empty unordered map mp to store each element and its latest index.
3. Traverse the array nums from index 0 to n-1.
4. For each element nums[i]:
       Check if nums[i] already exists in the map.
       If it exists:
       Calculate the distance between the current index and the previous index:
       distance = i - mp[nums[i]]
       If distance <= k, return true because a nearby duplicate is found.
       Update the map by storing the current index:
       mp[nums[i]] = i
5. If the loop completes without finding any nearby duplicate, return false.
6. End.

Code:
class Solution {
public:
    bool containsNearbyDuplicate(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        unordered_map<int,int>mp;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
            if(mp.find(nums[i])!=mp.end()){
                if(i-mp[nums[i]]<=k){
                     return true;
                }
            }
             mp[nums[i]]=i;  
            }
        return false;
    }
};
